Show HN: FedUp Feed Reader
text:
I wanted a way to test my blog's RSS feed, but couldn't find a easy solution that didn't require some form of subscription, login, or signup up so I made a simple Android app.

Along the way, I decided to make it a more functional by adding background refresh, notification, OPML import, offline viewing, and light/dark mode. I do plan on maintaining this project, and your feedback is very much appreciated.

Show HN: Subaligner – A multilingual subtitle generator
text: Subaligner has gone beyond subtitle synchronisation by starting transcribing audiovisual content with LLMs and generating near-production quality subtitles in a range of languages and formats (subaligner -m transcribe ...). More LLMs continually advancing over time will be made available after evaluation and stay tuned pls. What’s next after Whisper, Kaldi?

Can I use university provided laptop for working on my own startup?
text: I was given a laptop from the University where I am currently working towards my PhD. My professor approved a laptop for me from his available funds. The co-ordinator of the lab ordered it from Apples's website and it was first vetted and secured by the IT staff of the department. I am currently in my 3rd year and I came up with a product idea, unrelated to my dissertation. I am working on the idea using my university laptop, will that be an issue in the future, especially if I start full-time on my product (in case it works out).

Ask HN: What are you doing differently post-SVB?
text:
The Fed has just announced that they're backstopping SVB's depositors beyond the $250k FDIC amount. What are you doing differently in the wake of this incident?

Are you diversifying your banking relationships since the possibility of a run is now on your radar?

Are you not diversifying because they just saved SVB (and announced some new programs that should protect against this sort of incident happening in the future), so you expect it would be less likely than before?

How do people feel about doing business with SVB in particular? Some people said that opening a commercial account with them required exclusivity — is this true/will it be enforced going forward?

Are there any silver linings to this scare?
